Todd,<br><br>
I was a tunnel rat.  I'm not sure what you want to know.  I will answer specific questions.<br><br>
I was a Wolfhound in Cu Chi.  I can tell you that a lot of us volunteered to go into the tunnels.  It was part of who we were.  When bigger tunnel complexes were found the 65th Engineers were called in.  <br><br>
A tunnel complex was built in our base camp in Cu Chi in 1967 to teach people of the dangers etc., but it was just a beginning.  <br><br>
We were told once that we were looking for a tunnel that was over 11,000 meters long running from Vietnam into Cu Chi (Operation Cedar Falls).  We didn't find it.  The longest tunnel I entered was 300 meters long.<br><br>
Like I said before I will answer any questions you have.<br><br>
Paul<br><br>

